            <div class="info-box">
                <strong>Instructions:</strong> Pick one good molecule and one toxic molecule from the menus below to compare them side-by-side.<br><br>
                <strong>Look at "Molecular Mimicry":</strong> This shows which safe molecules the toxic ones copy! When a toxic molecule has a similar size and shape to a safe molecule, it can trick body proteins into grabbing it. Example: CO (28 g/mol, linear) tricks blood proteins because it looks like O₂ (32 g/mol, linear). The proteins can't tell the difference!
            </div>
            
            <!-- Selectors -->
            <div class="selectors-grid">
                <div class="selector-section beneficial">
